  1. Interpret the results of the model based on the coefficient for AVGFACSAL and the model \(p\)-value and adjusted \(r\)-squared value.

The p-value is essential zero and hte r-squared value is 0.02962, thus we can conclude that the likelihood of the observed differences due to chance is too small. The small r-squared value suggests that the AVGFACSAL in the regression model is not effectively explaining the variation in ICLEVEL

  1. Given the adjusted \(r\)-squared value, what do you recommend to try to better predict average earnings of working students ten years after initial enrollment at ICLEVEL 1 schools?

Given the small r-squared value, I would recommend a larger sample size to try to minize larger discrepencies in the data.
